President Trump visited Bakersfield, California to announce historic action on behalf of farmers and ranchers in the Central Valley. He addressed the issue of water access and the mismanagement of water resources in the state. He emphasized that California has an abundance of water, but it is not being properly utilized due to outdated regulations and policies. The President promised to solve the water crisis and provide farmers with the necessary water to support their crops and livelihoods. He also highlighted the importance of trade deals, such as the one with China, in boosting the agricultural industry. The President signed a presidential memorandum to address the water allocation issue and streamline the regulatory process for critical infrastructure projects, including water projects. He concluded by expressing his support for American farmers and ranchers and vowing to fight for their interests.